 The Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) disclosed this on its verified Twitter handle on Wednesday.  The football governing body said the striker Grade 2 Medial Collateral Ligament strain, adding that Oshoala will travel back to Spain on Thursday.  “Sad news from @NGSuper_Falcons camp: Top striker Asisat Oshoala is out of the ongoing WAFCON 2022. “She sustained a Grade 2 Medial Collateral Ligament strain in the game against South Africa. She is due back in Spain on Thursday. Get well quick Asisat!,“ NFF wrote.  Meanwhile, the Falcons hope to bounce back from their defeat to South Africa when they take on debutants and Group C leaders, Botswana on Thursday.  This year’s WAFCON also doubles as qualifiers for next year’s Women’s World Cup in Australia and New Zealand.